Hi - is it expected that the following requires lint pragmas?
t[0] is not assigned by the loop which assigns as far as maximum index [nn+1] == L2BITS 

```
module inv(y, a);

  parameter integer                                 BITS = 32;
  localparam integer                              L2BITS = $clog2(BITS);

  output logic                                [BITS-1:0] y;
  input  wire                                 [BITS-1:0] a;

  // verilator lint_off UNOPTFLAT
  wire                              [L2BITS:0][BITS-1:0] t;
  // verilator lint_on UNOPTFLAT

  assign t[0] = a;

  for (genvar nn=0; nn < L2BITS; nn++)
    assign t[nn+1] = ~t[nn];

   assign y = t[L2BITS];

endmodule

```
Verilator 4.100 2020-09-07 rev v4.040-74-g16fba5948

% verilator -cc -sv inv.sv

Thanks
